	"summary": "Security update for s390-tools",
	"details": "\nThis update of s390-tools fixes the following issues:\n\n- Fixed KMIP plugin failing to connection to KMIP server.\n\n  When a zkey key repository is bound to the KMIP plugin, and the\n  connection to the KMIP server is to be configired using command \n  'zkey kms configure --kmip-server <server>', it fails to connect\n  to the specified KMIP server.  (bsc#1199649)\n\n- rebuild with new secure boot key due to grub2 boothole 3 issues (bsc#1198581)\n",
